&lt;p&gt;I started looking at gitignore-reader/codeowners a bit, but it wasn&apos;t clear to me whether this was a problem in gitignore-reader or in the way rat is using it, so figured I&apos;d report it here to be sure &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; What am I doing differently than you?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &apos;/foo&apos; directory where my project is checked out is really at the filesystem root. This is indeed a bit exotic, but I ran into this building a project that uses this plugin in a sandbox.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess you could:&lt;/p&gt;

